  The present resolved resonance evaluation is a result of a      4825 1451
consistent analysis of available experimental information on Cd   4825 1451
isotopes together with simultaneous resonance optimization of     4825 1451
natural-Cd transmission and capture data measured at GELINA. The  4825 1451
R-matrix code REFIT has been used for resonance analysis.         4825 1451
  Resolved resonance parameters in MF=2 are REFIT (v.2008) output 4825 1451
parameters translated into ENDF-6 Reich-Moore format (LRU=1,LRF=3)4825 1451
  The code REFEND (v.July 2008) has been used for the translation 4825 1451
(format-conversion). The REFIT cross-sections are preserved in    4825 1451
ENDF provided that NJOY-compatible channel- and scattering-radius 4825 1451
options have been chosen by the REFIT evaluator. Conversion below 4825 1451
is rigorous/exact because of such compatibility.                  4825 1451
  A full description of the resolved resonance evaluation         4825 1451
performed at the EC-JRC-IRMM, Geel, Belgium, is given in Ref.1.   4825 1451
